deck: Descendant of Christ's bloodline, enforcer for the Vatican.
description:
Mariella was sent by Cardinal Innocent to kill the bearer of the Darkness, Jackie Estacado. Her mother, Rosalia, the previous Magdalena, had only just died, and so Rosalia was sent out into the field ahead of schedule with incomplete training. Her first encounter with the Darkness wielder ended in disaster and resulted in the Spear of Destiny being broken. Three other sisters from the Order of the Magdalene came to assist her, but the Darkness still emerged victorious.

Mariella managed to recover from the ordeal and received word that the Spear was in a secret location in the Amazon jungle. Upon traveling to the Spear's location in order to retrieve it, she ended up facing the Angelus, Lauren Franchetti, as well as her daughter Appolonia who wielded the Spear and chose to use it for darkness. As the battle progressed, the Magdalena was able to prevail against the Angelus' warriors but could not gain the upper hand against the combined forces of the Angelus and her daughter. Lauren then chooses to give herself completely to the Angelus entity and rather than choosing to face her daughter for embracing the Darkness, she flees from the battle. Mariella apparently survived the confrontation and was successful in recovering the Spear.
name: Sister Mariella

deck: Descendant of Christ, and enforcer for the Vatican. Mother of her successor as Magdalena, Sister Mariella.
description:
Rosalia was called into active duty to investigate a vampire rumor surrounding a number of killings in France. Confronted with the so called vampires, she learned that they were in fact affected by a rare disease which had shunned them from society. Rosalia intended to help them but by then she had called on the agents of the Inquisition, the Garduna, who made a move to eliminate the alleged vampire coven. Rosalia had no choice but to battle with their former employers who eventually took her life.

It was later revealed that as a teenager, Rosalia was raped and gave birth to a daughter who was taken from her and brought up in a convent. This child, Mariella eventually took her mother's place as the second Magdalena.

deck: Agent of W.A.N.D. and its director's right-hand man. He can alter people's memories with his Mouth of Madness and Mismemory.
description:
Origin

Creation

Todd was created by writers Ben Acker and Ben Blacker, and artist Matteo Lolli. He first appeared in 2014's Thunderbolts Annual #1.

Major Story Arcs

Thunderbolts

When it appeared that Doctor Strange was slowly enslaving the world into a mindless state of magical happiness, Thunderbolt Ross mobilized his team of Thunderbolts to take the Sorcerer Supreme out. To do this, the Thunderbolts needed to arm themselves with magical items to match Strange's might. While the Thunderbolts were successful in acquiring certain items, W.A.N.D. wound up helping them more than they would ever know. Taken to W.A.N.D. headquarters with a magical spell, Ross and the Leader met Director Pandora Peters and her right hand, Todd. The two Thunderbolts were magically restrained to prevent them from causing trouble, but were also given free rein of W.A.N.D.'s stores of magical weaponry and artifacts. After getting what they needed, Peters had Todd wipe the Thunderbolts' memory of their meeting, and replaced it with a memory of them getting their artifacts from a magical cache of Doctor Druid.

The Thunderbolts eventually proved victorious against the mad Doctor Strange, except that he turned out to actually be Oberoth'm'gozz in disguise, the True King of Faeries who sought to conquer Earth with his legion of Old Ones. Peters and her agents of W.A.N.D. soon arrived after the king's defeat to clean up the magical mess he'd left, and to bring back the real Doctor Strange. Peters reintroduced herself to the Thunderbolts and apologized for not handling the situation themselves, as they didn't know it wasn't actually Doctor Strange who was the threat. Afterwards though she had Todd wipe their memories once again, making them forget about their battle with Oberoth'm'gozz and replaced it with one of the Thunderbolts having a nice lunch of shawarma together.

Powers & Abilities

As an agent of WAND, Todd is presumably well versed in magic - both its lore and practical use. He also possesses the "Mouth of Madness and Mismemory," which allows him to magically erase and alter a person's memories however he chooses.
name: Todd

Origin

Lee Granger, scientist / adventurer, flies over the deep, jungle to find the Arab slave traders.

His plane crashes, and he becomes friendly with a tribe of Pygmies. He teaches them modern science, and through his ingenuity, give the power of speech to Eric, his faithful lion.

After saving the Pygmies from the slave traders, they make him their king.
